A '''Kerts-Bhrg generator''' was a large, cone-shaped power amplification device designed to project a field of energy capable of withstanding extreme levels of [[Star/Legends|stellar]] [[Radiation/Legends|radiation]].

==Characteristics==
When a central control generator was aligned with four similar devices, they could generate a three-dimensional force field in the shape of a pyramid. The walls of the force field could withstand temperatures in excess of 8,000 degrees. The field projection radius was variable, and could be expanded large enough to envelop an entire star fleet.

Each generator was equipped with a maintenance station containing base-mounted solar collectors, which tapped into the [[Ultraviolet/Legends|ultraviolet]] [[Radiation/Legends|radiation]] of a nearby [[Star/Legends|star]]. The central control generator, universally located at the apex of each pyramid, was equipped with a thruster system that could counteract the centrifugal force generated by the [[Gravity/Legends|gravitational]] pull of a nearby star. By doing so, the Kerts-Bhrg generator was able to maintain a geosynchronous [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]] within a star's corona.

==History==
Shortly after the establishment of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] base on [[Arbra/Legends|Arbra]] in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] had a Kerts-Bhrg pyramid field projected around the entire fleet. This allowed their ships to effectively hide from [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces by passing through the chromosphere of the [[Arbran]] sun.

Hours after establishing the field however, an absorption circuit on the central generator overloaded, greatly diminishing power to the field. Noxious fumes flooded the command station, knocking out all of the maintenance personnel. [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], unaffected by the fumes, were forced to run conduit cables between one of the Rebel ships and the control generator in order to stabilize the field's power fluctuations.

The ''[[Star Home]]'' made use of six Kerts-Bhrg generators.

